International superstar pop singer, Rihanna has hailed the dancing talents of a group of Ikorodu-based Nigerian kid dancers. Rihanna made two post of the kids, one was a dance video where the kids were seen dancing to DJ Spinall and Wizkid’s song, “Nowo”. The dance video was used to celebrate her achievement as the first female artiste to reach 2 billion streams worldwide. She shared the video and wrote; It is believed that Rihanna used the lit dance video of the kids to depict the goodness of God. See Video Below;  Meanwhile, Rihanna second post of the Kids was in response to their attitude of gratitude towards her decision to put them in the fore-front of over 60 million followers. Rihanna posted a photo of the kids holding placard to appreciate her gesture towards making them worldwide dance sensation. She posted a group photo of the kids and wrote; See her post Below;  The post #NigeriaToTheWorld: Rihanna Hails Ikorodu Kid Dancers (WATCH VIDEO) appeared first on 360Nobs.com. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 360Nobs.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.